      "message": "This breaks selections for diffs. Try selecting content from one side of a diff (in side-by-side mode) and observe that content from both sides becomes selected.\n\nQuoting from the Polymer 2 upgrade guide [1] the equivalence between ::content and ::slotted is that ..\n\n\u003e That is:\n\u003e\n\u003e  ::slotted(.foo)\n\u003e\n\u003e is equivalent to:\n\u003e\n\u003e  ::content \u003e .foo\n\n.. note the `\u003e` operator, meaning that the parameter of ::slotted must be an immediate child of the slot.\n\nSo, since the parameters to ::slotted used here (i.e. .content .contextControl and .blame) are not immediate children of the slot, this does not select them. One quick way to fix the styles is to add `* ` before each parameter.\n\n .contentWrapper ::slotted(* .content),\n .contentWrapper ::slotted(* .contextControl),\n .contentWrapper ::slotted(* .blame) {\n\n* [1] https://www.polymer-project.org/2.0/docs/upgrade#shadow-dom-styles",
